---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '../../../components/PageHero.astro';

const involvement = [
  {
    title: 'Family therapy sessions',
    body: [
      'Family therapy is part of the treatment plan, scheduled with your teen’s therapist as care begins. Sessions build shared language for what your teen is experiencing, work on communication and conflict, and give parents concrete ways to support their teen between sessions.',
      'The structure is set through assessment and the individual treatment plan, and it adjusts as care progresses.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Skill-building for parents',
    body: [
      'Parents and caregivers build the same DBT skills their teen is practicing: mindfulness, distress tolerance, emotional regulation, and interpersonal effectiveness.',
      'When the adults at home share the language and the tools, the skills are easier to keep using after a hard week, and the work in session connects to what happens at the kitchen table.',
    ],
  },
];

const focusAreas = [
  { title: 'Communication patterns', body: 'How family members talk and listen to each other, including the patterns that tend to escalate, and how to repair after conflict.' },
  { title: 'Role clarity', body: 'Understanding each person’s role in the family system, and where those roles may have become rigid or unhelpful.' },
  { title: 'Parenting approaches', body: 'What developmentally appropriate support looks like at this stage, especially for parents of younger adolescents.' },
  { title: 'Processing', body: 'Making room for what the whole family is carrying.' },
];
---

<Base
  bodyClass="brand-page"
  title="Family Therapy in Teen PHP & IOP | Joshua Tree Health"
  description="Family involvement is built into treatment at Joshua Tree Health in Apex, NC. How family sessions and parent skill-building support teen PHP and IOP."
>
  <PageHero
    title="Families are part of <em>the work.</em>"
    sub="Family involvement is built into every treatment plan, because what happens at home between sessions shapes what treatment can hold."
    art="session"
    primaryCta={{ label: 'Start the conversation', href: '/get-started' }}
  />

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="family-meaning-title">
    <div class="container-x prose" data-reveal>
      <h2 id="family-meaning-title">When one person is struggling, the whole family feels it.</h2>
      <p>Family systems therapy starts from a simple idea: a person does not exist in isolation. The relationships, patterns, and dynamics inside a family shape how each member thinks, feels, and behaves. Those patterns are often where the most important work happens.</p>
      <p>Family involvement at Joshua Tree begins with the first conversation and continues through discharge planning. That is not because we think the family caused the problem. It is because what happens at home between sessions matters as much as what happens in the room.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section surface-cream-deep" aria-labelledby="involvement-title">
    <div class="container-x">
      <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">Built in</p>
        <h2 class="section-title font-display" id="involvement-title">What family involvement includes.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-2" data-reveal-group>
        {involvement.map((item) => (
          <article class="info-card" data-reveal-item>
            <h3 class="info-card__title">{item.title}</h3>
            {item.body.map((p) => (
              <p class="info-card__body">{p}</p>
            ))}
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
      <!-- TODO: VERIFY family-session frequency before publishing any cadence. No weekly or 1:1 session promises until confirmed. -->
      <!-- TODO: VERIFY the current format and availability of caregiver DBT skills programming before naming a Parent DBT Skills Group or promising a parallel group schedule. -->
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="outcomes-title">
    <div class="container-x prose" data-reveal>
      <h2 id="outcomes-title">What happens at home matters.</h2>
      <p>Teens practice skills in the hours between sessions. Family work gives everyone a shared way to name what is happening and respond when conflict rises. It also gives parents a place to ask what support should look like now.</p>
      <p>Family therapy does not assign blame. It connects the work in the room to the relationships where a teen lives every day.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section surface-cream-deep" aria-labelledby="family-focus-title">
    <div class="container-x">
      <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
        <p class="eyebrow">In session</p>
        <h2 class="section-title font-display" id="family-focus-title">What families work on.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-2" data-reveal-group>
        {focusAreas.map((area) => (
          <article class="info-card" data-reveal-item><h3>{area.title}</h3><p>{area.body}</p></article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="ages-title">
    <div class="container-x prose" data-reveal>
      <h2 id="ages-title">How the work changes with age.</h2>
      <p>Parents of pre-teens often carry different questions than parents of older teens. With younger clients, roughly ages 10–12, family work leans more on the adults: at that stage, a steady parent nearby is often what helps a child settle, so we work closely with parents on what to do in hard moments.</p>
      <p>With older teens, ages 13–17, the work shifts toward autonomy. Family sessions help parents stay connected while making more room for identity, peer relationships, and increasing independence.</p>
      <p>Programming is developmentally appropriate across ages 10–17, and our admissions team will explain how groups are organized for your child&rsquo;s age.</p>
      <p><a class="link-arrow" href="/what-we-offer/our-approach">← Return to our full approach</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section surface-green" aria-labelledby="family-cta-title">
    <div class="container-x">
      <div class="section-head section-head--center" data-reveal>
        <h2 class="section-title font-display" id="family-cta-title">Family involvement starts on day one.</h2>
        <p class="section-sub">When you call, we&rsquo;ll talk about your teen and about how you&rsquo;re doing, because both matter.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn btn--on-dark" href="/get-started">Start the conversation <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn--ghost-on-dark" href="tel:+19193355053">Call (919) 335-5053</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .cta-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.6rem; }
</style>
